<HEADLINE>
ICE CREAM CHAIN TO GIVE AWAY CAPPUCCINO DRINK
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
BY DEBORAH ADAMSON  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ In a promotion sure to cause a major brain freeze
or two in overeager customers, Baskin-Robbins is giving away free
Cappuccino Blasts at 180 of its ice cream stores after 5 p.m.
today.
</P>
<P>
   The company said it wants to say thanks to customers for
supporting them over the years.
</P>
<P>
   By giving away the coffee-flavored ice cream drink,
Baskin-Robbins also wants to tell consumers that its stores sell
more than traditional frozen treats, a spokesman said. In recent
years, the company has expanded its menu of beverages to include
smoothies and a variety of ice cream coffee beverages.
</P>
<P>
   The company's Cappuccino Blast faces competition from the likes
of Starbucks and Coffee Bean &AMP; Tea Leaf, which serve iced coffee
drinks, and rivals like Jamba Juice and the Juice Club for its
smoothies.
</P>
<P>
   Baskin-Robbins expects to give away 30,000 gallons of Cappuccino
Blast today. To find the nearest participating store, call (800)
456-3332. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
