   MCCARTY-COLUMN _ DAYTON, Ohio _ My son counted down the weeks
and days leading up to the Big 7th Birthday Party. ``How many days
now, Mom? How many days?'' I opened my mouth, and my mother started
speaking: ``Don't wish your life away.'' Adults look at time from
the other end of the telescope. It's mere moments since our
children were born, and only a few weeks since we were kids
ourselves. Yet, as we tick off each day's tasks like items on a
grocery list, we still find ourselves wishing our lives away.
(McCarty, Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
