<TEXT>
<P>
   THE ``INTERNATIONAL'' TRAVELS OF PRESIDENT CLINTON
</P>
<P>
   -- In March, Clinton visited six African nations _ Ghana,
Uganda, Rwanda, South Africa, Botswana and Senegal _ on a journey
scripted to spotlight the promise and hope lying before a
long-tortured continent whose ties to the United States are rooted
in the savage beginnings of American slavery.
</P>
