   CIR-CONDUCTORS-COAT (Undated) _ A student at the MIT Media Lab
came up with a ``conductor's jacket'` that monitors the wearer's
breathing and other vitals, then converts them into some sort of
visual signal that can be displayed on a screen. Then she managed
to convince the head of the Boston Pops to wear it.
