<HEADLINE>
&HT;        BOXER BILL URGES MORE RESEARCH INTO SILICON BREAST IMPLANTS
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;     By Robin Brown  
 &HT;    c. 1998 States News Service  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Washington, June 10 -- Talk show host Jenny Jones -- live via
satellite from Los Angeles -- joined Sen. Barbara Boxer, D-Calif.,
to introduce legislation calling for a three-pronged approach to
insure women seeking breast implants have comprehensive, unbiased
information before making any decisions.
</P>
<P>
   ``We want to make sure women have the information up front,''
said Boxer. ``Women need accurate and complete information to make
informed choices and to get appropriate medical treatment,
especially cancer survivors who chose implants after surgery only
to suffer all over again.'' Women who have gotten silicon implants
have come forward with a variety of health problems, often serious.
Hundreds of thousands of women have filed lawsuits against Dow
Corning and other silicon implant manufacturers, claiming multiple
ailments. Boxer said there needs to be more independent study on
these adverse effects of the implants.
</P>
<P>
   The bill would encourage the National Institutes of Health to
expand research programs, create a Presidential committee to
coordinate federal agencies, and would insure that women have
access to the most up-to-date, complete information on implants
from their doctors.
</P>
<P>
   Jones, who has had five breast implants over the course of ten
years, said having access to independent, accurate information is
crucial to making safe decisions -- information she didn't get in
time.
</P>
<P>
   Calling breast implants the biggest mistake of her life, Jones
said, ``If I had the information I would not be where I am today.''
</P>
<P>
   Each time she had the implant surgery, the doctors assured her
it was safe. But each time -- whether the implants ruptured or the
silicon leaked, eventually sticking to her rib cage -- the surgery
proved far from safe, Jones said.
</P>
<P>
   ``I feel like a walking time bomb because I don't know what's
going to happen,'' she said angrily.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-06-10-98 1634EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
