<P>
   UNDATED _ Texas exports were up 13.2 percent in the first
quarter of 1998 from the same period a year ago, outpacing national
export growth by almost 3-to-1, says the Texas Department of
Economic Development. Texas exports, a key measure of the state's
economic health, hit $22.2 billion in the first quarter and are on
track to surpass 1997's record of $84.3 billion. By BILL BOWEN.
Story has moved in ``f'' financial category. &QL; 
