Mary Thweatt put her left (non-dominant) hand to paper and pencil,
closed her eyes and let her heart guide her through ``the horror''
of breast cancer. Thweatt, 81, drew did the art work five years ago
following the removal of her right breast and three-month
chemotherapy. The results are simple but powerful universal
depictions of cancer -- a disease some 10 million Americans have
endured. The drawings will be on display during Emory's Cancer
Survivors Day Saturday. (Guthrie, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
