<SLUG> BC-VIDEO-SPOTLIGHT11-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Spotlight on ``Afterglow'''s Julie Christie
 &HT;    By Steve Murray
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   -- ``Darling'': She won an Oscar as best actress for her role as
a pouty, jet-set fashion model.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Doctor Zhivago'': As Lara, the heroine responsible for that
annoying theme.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Petulia'': As a swinging-'60s San Franciscan, torn between
hubby Richard Chamberlain and older man George C. Scott.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``McCabe &AMP; Mrs. Miller'': As a frontier madame opposite
Warren Beatty in Robert Altman's hypnotic take on the Old West.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Don't Look Now'': Vacationing in Venice with husband Donald
Sutherland in a creepy tale of horror.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Shampoo'': As one of Beatty's many conquests in this
bittersweet '70s comedy about infidelity.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Heaven Can Wait'': She's the environmentalist, Beatty's the
quarterback in his romantic comedy.
</P>
