   ENDANGERED-SPECIES (Undated) The Clinton Administration's
trademark new approach to implementing enforcement of the
Endangered Species Act on millions of acres of private lands across
the United States has relied upon shaky science, a new study has
found.The draft study, performed by 119 independent scientists with
National Science Foundation funding, highlights scientific
weaknesses in Habitat Conservation Plans, which the administration
has used to enforce the ESA. The plans, or HCPs, are negotiated
agreements that allow landowners to destroy habitat and even kill
imperilled species _ by logging or home-building for instance _ in
return for land management improvements that may help the plants or
animals at risk.
