<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of Thursday, June 11 and thereafter. The stories will carry the
``f'' financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For
questions about stories, contact James Laurin at the Daily News,
(818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   KOO-KOO-ROO (Los Angeles) _ The privately held parent company of
Chi-Chi's and El Torito restaurants said it is buying Koo Koo Roo
Inc. for $158.3 million in stock and assumed debt. Lee Iacocca, the
former Chrysler boss who was named Koo Koo Roo's acting chairman
two months ago, called the transaction ``an ideal strategic fit.''
But Wall Street apparently doesn't agree. By Deborah Adamson.
</P>
<P>
   GALLERIA-MAKEOVER (Los Angeles) _ The San Fernando Valley mall
that gave birth to the Valley Girl is, like, getting a totally
dramatic makeover. By Gregory J. Wilcox.
</P>
