<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Meet the players
 &HT;    By Wendy Parker
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Claudio Reyna
</P>
<P>
   Country: U.S. Age: 24.
</P>
<P>
   Position: Midfielder.
</P>
<P>
   Club team: VfL Wolfsburg (Germany).
</P>
<P>
   Notes: Designated the midfield creator by U.S. coach Steve
Sampson, who cut captain John Harkes to make room for Reyna's
talents. Is recovering from a groin pull, the latest in a series of
injuries that have plagued his career. He missed the 1994 World Cup
with a strained hamstring. A member of the 1996 U.S. Olympic team.
Played three years at the University of Virginia before heading to
Germany.
</P>
