<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-CLIPPERS-BIBBY-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CLIPPERS TAKE SNEAK PEEK AT BIBBY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Clippers had the privilege of working out Mike Bibby on
Tuesday. It's the only NBA team the talented University of Arizona
point guard has allowed to have a private glimpse of his skills.
</P>
<P>
   It may have been his only pre-draft performance, but Bibby
appeared anything but nervous while on display in a morning workout
at USC.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's been a lifelong dream to go through this situation,''
Bibby said. ``When I was in high school, I was just happy to get a
scholarship in college. I didn't really care about it when I made
my decision to turn pro, but this is unbelievable.''
</P>
<P>
   The Clippers are expected to make Bibby the top pick in the
draft, which is June 24. Asked if he thought the Clippers would
select him, Bibby said, ``I hope.''
</P>
<P>
   With team executives Elgin Baylor and Andy Roeser inside USC's
Lyon Center, Bibby worked out for approximately an hour.
</P>
<P>
   ``He has a good feel for the game and is in excellent shape,''
Baylor said. ``I don't think he did anything that surprised me.
He's probably got more overall speed and quickness than he had in
college.''
</P>
<P>
   Ironically, Bibby's father, USC coach Henry Bibby, showed up at
the Lyon Center to play racquetball just as Mike Bibby concluded
his workout. If the Clippers select him, Mike Bibby said his family
would move from Arizona to Los Angeles, including his baby son,
Michael Dane, and his mother, Virginia.
</P>
<P>
   There still remains the possibility the Clippers will trade the
No. 1 pick, but that prospect didn't faze Mike Bibby. ``It doesn't
matter,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Baylor said he expects to get more trade proposals as the draft
approaches.
</P>
<P>
   ``There's a lot of things that could happen,'' Baylor said.
``Offers will increase. You just don't know what's going to
happen.''
</P>
<P>
   Baylor denied reports that Orlando has offered point guard
Anfernee Hardaway for the No. 1 pick. There are also rumors that
San Antonio might offer center David Robinson.
</P>
<P>
   Baylor said the Clippers will work out 19 players before the
draft, including Bibby. The Clippers also own the 22nd pick in the
draft.
</P>
<P>
   Among the other players the Clippers have looked at are
Minnesota guard Sam Jacobson, Kansas swingman Paul Pierce, Pacific
center Michael Olowokandi, Michigan forward Robert Traylor, UCLA
center Jelani McCoy, Ball State guard Bonzi Wells and Cincinnati
guard Ruben Patterson.
</P>
<P>
   As for the Clippers' coaching situation, Baylor would not say
when he will hire a replacement for Bill Fitch. Former Seattle
coach George Karl is the top choice, and has received permission to
talk to the Clippers. Karl is expected to wait until the NBA Finals
are completed, though, to see what other job offers may exist.
</P>
<P>
   Another prospective candidate, former Phoenix coach Paul
Westphal, now appears to be the front-runner to replace Karl in
Seattle. Westphal said last week he believed the Sonics would make
a decision before the draft.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
